thread.title: Subway Worker Dies in Tunnel Fall in Harlem

author: Paul Berger
title: Subway Worker Dies in Tunnel Fall in Harlem
text:
A 23-year-old New York City subway worker died after falling onto tracks in Harlem early Tuesday, according to law enforcement.
The worker sustained head injuries after falling from a height while working inside a tunnel close to the 125th Street station on the 4, 5 and 6 lines, according to the New York Police Department.
